2. Volatilitet

2.1

Modsat en AR model så modellere man sin noise process i en GARCH model, hvilket giver mulighed for at fange volatility clusters osv.

2.2

# volatilitet <- rio::import("week10-selfstudy/volatilitet.csv")
volatilitet <- rio::import("volatilitet.csv")

return <- volatilitet$aktiekurs %>% log() %>% diff()
plot(return)

acf(return)

acf(abs(return))

qqnorm(return)
qqline(return)

kurtosis(return)
## [1] 9.241252
kurtosis(rnorm(n = 2010,mean(return),sd(return)))
## [1] -0.0804995
ggplot(data.frame(return = return, normal = rnorm(n = 2010,mean(return),sd(return)))) +
  geom_density(aes(x = return), color = "blue") +
  geom_density(aes(x = normal), color = "red")
